WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.099 --> 00:00:05.680
Robert Kuok Hock Nien, is an influential Malaysian
Chinese businessman.

00:00:05.680 --> 00:00:12.750
According to Forbes his net worth is estimated
to be around $14.7 billion on Feb 2012, making

00:00:12.750 --> 00:00:18.520
him the richest person in Malaysia and second
richest in Southeast Asia after Dhanin Chearavanont

00:00:18.520 --> 00:00:23.760
of Thailand, according to Forbe's List of
World Billionaires 2013 which Robert Kuok

00:00:23.760 --> 00:00:25.000
was placed 76th.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:31.860
As of December 2012, According to the Bloomberg
Billionaires Index, Kuok has an estimated

00:00:31.860 --> 00:00:37.239
net worth of 17.3 billion making him the 40th
richest person in the world.

00:00:37.239 --> 00:00:43.620
Kuok is media-shy; most of his businesses
are privately held by him or his family.

00:00:43.620 --> 00:00:48.749
Apart from a multitude of businesses in Malaysia,
his companies have investments in many countries

00:00:48.749 --> 00:00:50.489
throughout Asia.

00:00:50.489 --> 00:00:56.410
His business interests range from sugarcane
plantations, sugar refineries, flour milling,

00:00:56.410 --> 00:01:04.589
animal feed, oil, mining, finance, hotels,
properties, trading, freight and publishing.

00:01:04.589 --> 00:01:09.140
Biggest source of wealth is stake in Wilmar
International, the world's largest listed

00:01:09.140 --> 00:01:11.200
palm oil company.

00:01:11.200 --> 00:01:17.440
He was a student from Raffles Institution
and English College Johore Bahru English collegian.

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:20.310
Family
Robert Kuok's son, Kuok Khoon Ean born in

00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:27.240
1955 married Kuok Cheng Sui and holds Bachelor
of Arts Degree in Economics from University

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:29.729
of Nottingham, England.

00:01:29.729 --> 00:01:35.670
His other son, Kuok Khoon Ho is the Chairman
of the Kuok Brothers, born in 1951 and holds

00:01:35.670 --> 00:01:40.649
Bachelor of Commerce degree, from McGill University,
Canada.

00:01:40.649 --> 00:01:46.320
Robert Kuok's brother, Tan Sri Dato' Philip
Kuok Hock Khee a Malaysian Ambassador to Bonn,

00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:52.950
Federal Republic of Germany, Yugoslavia, Netherlands,
Belgium, Luxembourg and Denmark was born on

00:01:52.950 --> 00:01:58.719
18 May 1921 and attended with Robert Kuok
to English College Johore Bahru before going

00:01:58.719 --> 00:02:03.939
to the College of Agriculture, Serdang and
later to the University of Malaya with a degree

00:02:03.939 --> 00:02:05.789
in Economics.

00:02:05.789 --> 00:02:10.691
Tan Sri Philip married Eileen Kuok and had
two sons and two daughters, he died on 16

00:02:10.691 --> 00:02:17.050
December 2003 and was awarded with Netherlands
award of the Grand Cross of the Order of Orange

00:02:17.050 --> 00:02:23.050
Nassau, and decorated with Dato' Sri Paduka
Mahkota Johor, Dato' Paduka Mahkota Johor

00:02:23.050 --> 00:02:24.810
and Panglima Setia Mahkota.

00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:28.550
Kuok has married twice and has eight children.

00:02:28.550 --> 00:02:33.600
His fourth eldest son, which he passed on
to be the holder of Shangri-la Hotels Jeffrey

00:02:33.600 --> 00:02:35.850
Ong Teng Buey married twice.

00:02:35.850 --> 00:02:37.870
He has three sons and a daughter.

00:02:37.870 --> 00:02:44.370
They are Justin Choo Jia Wei, Bryan Choo Jia
Jun, Jon Choo Jia Sheng and Alyssa Ong Lei

00:02:44.370 --> 00:02:45.370
Yeng.

00:02:45.370 --> 00:02:50.470
Kuok officially retired from the Kerry Group
on 1 April 1993.

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:56.860
One of his sons, Kuok Khoon Ean, now handles
most of the day-to-day operations of his businesses.

00:02:56.860 --> 00:02:59.550
He currently resides in Hong Kong.

00:02:59.550 --> 00:03:02.700
Biography
Robert Kuok has been the richest man in South

00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:05.470
East Asia since 2002.

00:03:05.470 --> 00:03:07.360
He is in the sugar business.

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:13.430
Kuok's father arrived in Malaya from Fujian,
China, at the beginning of the 20th century,

00:03:13.430 --> 00:03:20.570
and Robert was the youngest of three brothers,
born on 6 October 1923, in Johor Bahru.

00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:25.900
He grew up speaking his parents' Chinese Fuzhou
dialect, English and Japanese during Japan's

00:03:25.900 --> 00:03:28.530
wartime occupation of Malaya.

00:03:28.530 --> 00:03:33.410
He claims he began in business as an office
boy, and later started a business with relatives'

00:03:33.410 --> 00:03:34.410
support.

00:03:34.410 --> 00:03:39.890
Upon graduation, he worked as a clerk in the
rice-trading department of Japanese industrial

00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:47.300
conglomerate Mitsubishi Shoji Kaisha between
1942 and 1945, in Singapore, a conglomerate

00:03:47.300 --> 00:03:51.940
which with the help of Japanese military unit
monopolized the rice trade in Malaya during

00:03:51.940 --> 00:03:54.090
the occupation period.

00:03:54.090 --> 00:03:58.210
He was soon promoted to headed the rice-trading
department.

00:03:58.210 --> 00:04:02.730
After the war, he took the skills he learned
from the Japanese back to the family's business

00:04:02.730 --> 00:04:03.730
in Johor.

00:04:03.730 --> 00:04:10.260
Kuok senior died in 1948, and Kuok and his
two brothers and a cousin Kuok Hock Chin founded

00:04:10.260 --> 00:04:16.020
[Kuok Brothers Sdn Bhd] in 1949, trading agricultural
commodities.

00:04:16.020 --> 00:04:21.910
Kuok relationship with the Japanese continued
after Malaya gained independence.

00:04:21.910 --> 00:04:30.380
In 1959, Kuok formed Malayan Sugar Manufacturing
Co. Bhd. together with two prominent Japanese

00:04:30.380 --> 00:04:31.970
partners.

00:04:31.970 --> 00:04:37.040
He also brought many influential Malay elite
into his company as directors and shareholders

00:04:37.040 --> 00:04:40.410
which include UMNO politician and Malay royalty.

00:04:40.410 --> 00:04:44.970
Kuok was granted a monopoly of sugar production
in Malaysia.

00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:51.530
In 1961, he made a coup by buying cheap sugar
from India before the prices shot up.

00:04:51.530 --> 00:04:57.310
He continued to invest heavily in sugar refineries,
controlled 80% of the Malaysian sugar market

00:04:57.310 --> 00:05:03.730
with production of 1.5 million tonnes, equivalent
to 10% of world production, and so earned

00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:06.180
his nickname "Sugar King of Asia".

00:05:06.180 --> 00:05:11.760
In 1971, he built the first Shangri-La Hotel,
in Singapore.

00:05:11.760 --> 00:05:17.380
His first foray into Hong Kong property was
in 1977, when he acquired a plot of land on

00:05:17.380 --> 00:05:23.840
the newly reclaimed Tsim Sha Tsui East waterfront,
where he built the second hotel, the Kowloon

00:05:23.840 --> 00:05:25.100
Shangri-La.

00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:31.810
In 1993, his Kerry Group acquired a 34.9%
stake in the South China Morning Post from

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:34.440
Murdoch's News Corporation.

00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:40.740
His companies have investments in many countries,
including Singapore, the Philippines, Thailand,

00:05:40.740 --> 00:05:45.530
Mainland China, Indonesia, Fiji and Australia.

00:05:45.530 --> 00:05:50.380
Businesses in China include 10 bottling companies
for Coca Cola, and ownership of the Beijing

00:05:50.380 --> 00:05:52.560
World Trade Centre.

00:05:52.560 --> 00:05:56.680
Freight interests include Malaysian Bulk Carriers
Berhad and Transmile Group.

00:05:56.680 --> 00:06:01.290
His political influence is attested by his
having been selected as one of the Hong Kong

00:06:01.290 --> 00:06:06.380
Affairs Advisors in the run-up to the transfer
of sovereignty of Hong Kong, and his minority

00:06:06.380 --> 00:06:09.520
stake in CITIC Pacific.

00:06:09.520 --> 00:06:14.360
He was also instrumental in conveying information
and setting up the meetings between Malaysia

00:06:14.360 --> 00:06:19.890
and China governments leading to full diplomatic
cross recognition of the two countries.

00:06:19.890 --> 00:06:26.910
On 31 October 2009, PPB Group under the flagship
of Robert Kuok issued a statement to the Bursa

00:06:26.910 --> 00:06:31.320
Malaysia that it had decided to dispose of
its sugar units along with land used to cultivate

00:06:31.320 --> 00:06:35.940
sugar cane for RM 1.29 billion to FELDA.

00:06:35.940 --> 00:06:39.450
The sales resulted in a one-off gain for the
company.

00:06:39.450 --> 00:06:44.080
The sugar unit and sugar cane plantation were
the second largest business segment upon its

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:47.230
grain and feed which were topping the sales.

00:06:47.230 --> 00:06:54.130
In February 2014, Kuok's Singapore-based oil
services company PACC Offshore Services Holdings

00:06:54.130 --> 00:06:59.639
started pre-IPO talks with investors to list
on the Singapore Stock Exchange to raise $400

00:06:59.639 --> 00:07:00.639
million.

